      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The concept of directed, rapid cognitive evolution through radiation exposure is highly theoretical and touches on the edge of current biological understanding. We can certainly explore models where ionizing radiation interacts with DNA and promotes plasticity. Research into radiation response in extremophiles often involves DNA repair mechanisms and stress-response gene activation, which could theoretically influence neural pathways. We can look into studies on gene expression changes triggered by radiation to see what theoretical frameworks exist for such rapid biological shifts.",
